# kube-rbac-proxy

HTTP proxy sidecar providing Kubernetes RBAC-based authentication and authorization for metrics endpoints.

- **Upstream**: [brancz/kube-rbac-proxy](https://github.com/brancz/kube-rbac-proxy)
- **Downstream**: [openshift/kube-rbac-proxy](https://github.com/openshift/kube-rbac-proxy)
- **Not a standalone Deployment** — runs as a sidecar in Prometheus, Alertmanager, Prometheus Operator, kube-state-metrics, openshift-state-metrics, node-exporter, Thanos Querier, Thanos Ruler, telemeter-client

## How It Works

Client → kube-rbac-proxy (TokenReview + SubjectAccessReview) → Backend /metrics

## Investigation

If metrics endpoints return 401/403 errors, check kube-rbac-proxy logs on the affected component's pod. Common issues: expired tokens, missing RBAC bindings, API server connectivity.
